{
  "texts": [
    "To calculate reliability, standardized Cronbach's alpha was computed using a mixed model; Cronbach's alpha was.91 for internal details and.79 for external details.",
    "Data from these experiments include 27 younger adults (mean age = 22.59 years, SD = 3.18, 12 male) and 25 older adults (mean age = 72.24, SD = 6.49; seven male).",
    "Participants indicated no history of neurological or psychiatric impairment.",
    "These participants were recruited from Harvard University and the surrounding community, using the Harvard psychology study pool.",
    "van Genugten et al."
  ]
}